(1 comment)

After delving around in the config loading, this is oslo.config not parsing None correctly as a NoneType for a cfg.StrOpt option type (parses as the string 'None').

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

The change was introduced in https://review.openstack.org/#/c/150144 . Please include  the blueprint name, appropriate flags and the corresponding changes in the doc/.. file(s).

The new default works.

However, the main question is: 

this was intended to be a Rackspace-only change and then be adopted by other deployers if they really need to. I'm curious if such was the case with the gate; is there a good use case for testing this upstream?

Thanks!

Patch Set 1:

Nikhil: this wouldn't actually be tested in the gate if it was working as was intended when the change was made. The option should be ignored if it is set to NoneType, rather than the string 'None'.

Patch Set 1:

Nikhil,

I think commenting this out makes lots of sense while it's single vendor specific as the store works without it (and specially it breaking gate for others). I do think the doc being correct still (having it just commented out emphasizing it being optional). Also commenting it out will default to None rather than "None" which is the documented behavior.

Patch Set 1:

@Louis: I do not understand your point

"this wouldn't actually be tested in the gate if it was working as was intended when the change was made. "

It is either tested or not tested? It should be tested if it was something that openstack was using in general. 

My question was about it's use. It was originally a vendor specific use case however, that does not seem to be the case now.

The rest of the changes (flags, bp, etc) are not affected by this change. So, looks good as is.
